parameters:
Here is the reception for 'Immigration Applications'... I've been
really busy lately.

Welcomeee! Since I'm still in training, I'm only doing voice
acting for now!!

Ah, welcome! Now that my training is over, I can finally start
working too...!

Wow, here you can do subquests! ...But there are no collection
elements or anything like that. Surprisingly, it specializes in
ecchi subquests!!

Since it's gradually being added, please take a look when you
feel like it! Oh, there's no time limit, so feel free to check it
out whenever you want.

Be careful because the subquests start immediately when you
choose them. Hmm... something like that? I don't think there are
any other special precautions...
You like this kind of thing too, right?

Welcomeee!! Currently, here are the subquests that you can take
on!!

Welcomeee!! Currently, here are the available subquests that you
can take on!!

Oh dear, as a solo healer, there are no quests that I can
clear...

I heard that being a support class is recommended for beginners,
but I never expected there would be such pitfalls...

There are no subquests in this guild. Well, it has its pros and
cons... I'm fine with it being easy though.

It seems like I can do subquests now. It's different from what I
was expecting though... It doesn't matter to me. Because I'm not
popular.

Because I also have to carry a large amount of documents, working
at the government office is surprisingly physically demanding...
I love the guild because it's cool!
\SE[2]Oh... I've come to a place that seems reliable...

\SE[0]So this is the Adventurer's Guild. \SE[1]I think we'll be
relying on this place a lot since we can accept all quests here.

\SE[0]I think the receptionist will tell us, so let's first
listen to what they have to say.

Here, you can start the Main Quest. After accepting the quest,
the story will automatically begin, so please make sure to
prepare yourself before proceeding.

You can start all the 'Main Quests' from here. If you're not sure
about the next destination, try asking this person for now.

It seems this is your first time using our services... Well then,
I will give you the Transference Crystal!

Well, you see... It's a super convenient item that allows you to
warp to any place instantly, no matter how far away you are!

The Transference Crystal has become available on the menu screen.
You can quickly move to registered locations.

In general, it will be registered upon clearing a quest. However,
please note that some dungeons will not be registered.

There are times when you can't use it due to adult circumstances,
so please understand when that happens!
...In general, what she said is correct.

Currently, we have received a request for the Inspection of the
Beginner's Village. Would you like to start this quest?

Quests are something you just have to do to a certain extent.
Or... should I just teach you casually?

First, let's start with \i[105] subjugation quests. You can do
them once you have gained confidence in your abilities. There's
no particular time limit for these quests.

And next are gathering quests. You can do them while doing
something else, or if you find them bothersome, you don't have to
do them.

And \i[82] character quests. \!It might be better to prioritize
these. Your important person might be asking for help. \!That
could also be the case...
Well, that's the gist of it. Just do your best, okay...
Oh, well. Just do your best, okay...
\SE[2]Oh... I've come to a place that seems reliable...

\SE[0]So this is the Adventurer's Guild. \SE[1]I think we'll be
relying on this place a lot since we can accept all quests here.

\SE[0]I think the receptionist will tell us, so let's first
listen to what they have to say.
Oh, you're a newcomer. Here, we handle subquests.

If you're in a hurry to proceed, talk to the Black-haired Maid
over there.

Over here... it's about earning money, defeating bosses, and
\!having a lot of depth? \!For those who want to have fun? That
kind of feeling.

There might be times when acquaintances will request quests...?
There might even be strengthening quests...? \!They occasionally
get updated, so feel free to check them out when you feel like
it.
Let me explain the quests to you in a flash.

【Subjugation Quests】 \i[105] are quests with the icon that
require you to defeat specific strong monsters, it seems like?
\!You should decide based on your own abilities.

【Gathering Quests】 \i[247] have an icon that... umm... requires
you to collect specified items... or something like that? \!I'll
include hints on how to collect them in the Quest Details
section.

【Character Quests】 Finally, there's the one with the \i[82] icon.
After accepting it, make sure to talk to the client. \!The
content will be varied, I suppose.

Ah, I don't want to explain anymore, so if you don't
understand...
Just ask Priscilla-chan at the entrance, okay?

That's the general idea... umm... did you understand? Well, you
know, they say practice makes perfect, right? I'm sure you'll be
fine. Yeah.
Here are the Sub Quests that you can currently accept.
